'''Toby David Basner''' (born July 29, 1984) is an American professional [[baseball]] [[Umpire (baseball)|umpire]]. He umpired his first [[Major League Baseball]] (MLB) game on June 24, 2012.

==Early life and career==
Basner was born on July 29, 1984 in [[Bowling Green, Ohio]]. He graduated from [[Brookwood High School (Snellville, Georgia)|Brookwood High School]] in Georgia. He had been umpiring baseball games since the age of 12. He attended the [[Harry Wendelstedt Umpire School]] at the age of 19, where he was identified as an umpiring prospect by a professional evaluation course. He reported to the rookie-level [[Gulf Coast League]]. He spent several seasons in the lower minor leagues. He worked his first full season in [[Triple-A (baseball)|Triple-A]] in 2010.<ref name=Beitzel>{{cite news|last=Beitzel|first=Ben|title=Brookwood grad Basner climbing his way through minors in blue|url=http://www.gwinnettdailypost.com/news/2010/jul/08/brookwood-grad-basner-climbing-his-way-through/|accessdate=April 27, 2014|newspaper=[[Gwinnett Daily Post]]|date=July 8, 2010}}</ref>

Basner debuted in the major leagues on June 24, 2012.<ref name=RS>{{cite web|title=The 2012 ML Regular Season Umpiring Log for Toby Basner|url=http://www.retrosheet.org/boxesetc/2012/IUbasnt9010002012.htm|website=[[Retrosheet]]|accessdate=September 24, 2017}}</ref> Through the end of the [[2016 Major League Baseball season|2016 season]], Basner has umpired 323 MLB games, and has issued 11 [[Ejection (sports)|ejection]]s.

===Notable games===
During a game between the [[Toronto Blue Jays]] and [[Minnesota Twins]] on May 21, 2016, Toronto third baseman and reigning [[American League]] [[Major League Baseball Most Valuable Player Award|MVP]] [[Josh Donaldson]] made a comment towards the Minnesota dugout after a first inning groundout. Basner, thinking Donaldson was addressing him, ejected him from the game, a game Toronto would go on to lose.<ref>{{cite news |title=Jays’ Donaldson a victim of missed direction in loss to Twins |url=https://www.thestar.com/sports/bluejays/2016/05/21/twins-rally-against-jays-bullpen-score-five-in-eighth.html |first=Mark |last=Zwolinski |newspaper=Toronto Star |date=May 21, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FdyzUJKt4MI |title=TOR@MIN: Donaldson gets ejected in the 1st |publisher=[[MLB.com]] |date=May 21, 2016 |via=[[YouTube]]}}</ref> Basner's wife later bragged about the incident on social media, referring to her husband as a "boss"; she closed all of her social media accounts soon after.<ref>{{cite web |title=Wife of Ump who tossed Josh Donaldson from game Saturday brags about it on Facebook |url=http://www2.tsn.ca/bardown/Story.aspx?Wife%2Bof%2BUmp%2Bwho%2Btossed%2BJosh%2BDonaldson%2Bfrom%2Bgame%2BSaturday%2Bbrags%2Babout%2Bit%2Bon%2BFacebook&id=580545 |website=BarDown |date=May 21, 2016}}</ref> Crew chief [[Joe West (umpire)|Joe West]] referred to the incident as "the funniest darn ejection I’ve ever seen."<ref>{{cite news |title=Toronto Blue Jays cruise for seven innings before running aground against Minnesota Twins |url=http://news.nationalpost.com/sports/mlb/toronto-blue-jays-cruise-for-seven-innings-before-running-aground-against-minnesota-twins |newspaper=[[National Post]] |date=May 21, 2016}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Basner's father, Alan, is an umpire at the high school and college levels.<ref name=Beitzel/>

